# Testing and Error Handling

## Testing Strategy
- Write unit tests for utility functions
- Test React components with React Testing Library
- Test user interactions and form submissions
- Mock external dependencies and API calls
- Aim for meaningful test coverage, not just high percentages
- Use descriptive test names that explain the expected behavior

## Error Handling
- Implement proper error boundaries for React components
- Handle async errors with try-catch blocks
- Provide meaningful error messages to users
- Log errors appropriately for debugging
- Implement fallback UI states for error conditions
- Validate user inputs and API responses

## Loading States
- Implement loading states for async operations
- Use skeleton screens for better UX
- Disable buttons during form submission
- Show progress indicators for long operations
- Handle network timeouts gracefully

## Security Considerations
- Validate all user inputs on both client and server
- Sanitize data before displaying to users
- Never expose sensitive information in client-side code
- Use proper authentication and authorization patterns
- Implement rate limiting for API calls
- Follow OWASP security best practices

## Performance Monitoring
- Monitor Core Web Vitals
- Use Next.js built-in performance monitoring
- Implement proper error tracking (e.g., Sentry)
- Monitor API response times
- Track user interactions and conversion rates
- Use browser dev tools for performance profiling